      "text": [
        "175 - وَ رُوِيَ: «أَنَّ مَنْ قَصَدَ إِلَى مَصْلُوبٍ فَنَظَرَ إِلَيْهِ وَجَبَ عَلَيْهِ اَلْغُسْلُ عُقُوبَةً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.175 - It is narrated: 'Whoever deliberately goes to look at a crucified person must perform ghusl (ritual bathing) as a form of penance.'."
        ]
      }
    }
